        <description>&lt;img src="https://whhong-research.github.io/p/%E6%B5%B7%E4%B8%8A%E9%A3%8E%E6%9C%BA%E7%8A%B6%E6%80%81%E7%9B%91%E6%B5%8B%E4%B8%8E%E8%BF%90%E7%BB%B4%E7%AD%96%E7%95%A5%E4%BC%98%E5%8C%96%E5%9F%BA%E4%BA%8E%E6%88%90%E6%9C%AC%E6%95%88%E7%9B%8A%E7%9A%84%E7%BB%BC%E5%90%88%E5%86%B3%E7%AD%96%E6%A1%86%E6%9E%B6/1.png" alt="Featured image of post Offshore Wind Turbine Condition Monitoring and Maintenance Strategy Optimization: A Cost-Effectiveness Based Decision Framework" /&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Article Information&lt;/strong&gt;: This article is a reading note of the paper &lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;A generic framework for the optimisation of maintenance strategies for offshore wind turbines&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt;. This study constructs a generic framework for optimizing maintenance strategies for offshore wind turbines, with particular focus on the synergistic application of SCADA systems and dedicated Condition Monitoring Systems (CMS).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;research-background-and-core-questions&#34;&gt;Research Background and Core Questions
&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;research-objectives&#34;&gt;Research Objectives
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;This paper aims to address two key questions in offshore wind turbine operation and maintenance:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feasibility of Monitoring Systems&lt;/strong&gt;: Can SCADA systems in wind farms serve as a viable alternative to dedicated Condition Monitoring Systems (CMS)?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Integrated Optimization Strategy&lt;/strong&gt;: How can CMS be combined with O&amp;amp;M strategies to maximize the financial benefits of Offshore Wind Turbines (OWTs)?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;core-contributions&#34;&gt;Core Contributions
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;This research establishes a &lt;strong&gt;comprehensive simulation framework&lt;/strong&gt; capable of:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Simulating the degradation process of wind turbine components&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluating the detection capabilities of different monitoring systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimizing the cost-effectiveness ratio of maintenance strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;basic-model-assumptions&#34;&gt;Basic Model Assumptions
&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;health-state-classification&#34;&gt;Health State Classification
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The research divides the health state of each subsystem into &lt;strong&gt;four levels&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
  &lt;thead&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;th style=&#34;text-align: center&#34;&gt;State Level&lt;/th&gt;
          &lt;th style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Description&lt;/th&gt;
          &lt;th style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;O&amp;amp;M Impact&lt;/th&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/thead&gt;
  &lt;tbody&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: center&#34;&gt;Normal&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;No faults&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Normal operation&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: center&#34;&gt;Minor Fault&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Minor defects exist&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Allowed to continue operation&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: center&#34;&gt;Critical Fault&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Serious defects exist&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Can still operate, but needs attention&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: center&#34;&gt;Failure&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Complete failure&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Triggers shutdown&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Assumptions&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In minor fault and critical fault states, the subsystem is still allowed to operate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Critical faults are more easily detected by CMS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Different components have different false alarm rates at different stages of fault development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Any subsystem failure will trigger wind turbine shutdown&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;degradation-process-model&#34;&gt;Degradation Process Model
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The degradation process of each subsystem follows the &lt;strong&gt;Weibull Distribution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Parameters of the Weibull Distribution are derived from publicly available failure rate data in the literature&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://whhong-research.github.io/p/%E6%B5%B7%E4%B8%8A%E9%A3%8E%E6%9C%BA%E7%8A%B6%E6%80%81%E7%9B%91%E6%B5%8B%E4%B8%8E%E8%BF%90%E7%BB%B4%E7%AD%96%E7%95%A5%E4%BC%98%E5%8C%96%E5%9F%BA%E4%BA%8E%E6%88%90%E6%9C%AC%E6%95%88%E7%9B%8A%E7%9A%84%E7%BB%BC%E5%90%88%E5%86%B3%E7%AD%96%E6%A1%86%E6%9E%B6/image-20250303154521803.png&#34;
	width=&#34;874&#34;
	height=&#34;471&#34;
	srcset=&#34;https://whhong-research.github.io/p/%E6%B5%B7%E4%B8%8A%E9%A3%8E%E6%9C%BA%E7%8A%B6%E6%80%81%E7%9B%91%E6%B5%8B%E4%B8%8E%E8%BF%90%E7%BB%B4%E7%AD%96%E7%95%A5%E4%BC%98%E5%8C%96%E5%9F%BA%E4%BA%8E%E6%88%90%E6%9C%AC%E6%95%88%E7%9B%8A%E7%9A%84%E7%BB%BC%E5%90%88%E5%86%B3%E7%AD%96%E6%A1%86%E6%9E%B6/image-20250303154521803_hu_d6169eec14c02c29.png 480w, https://whhong-research.github.io/p/%E6%B5%B7%E4%B8%8A%E9%A3%8E%E6%9C%BA%E7%8A%B6%E6%80%81%E7%9B%91%E6%B5%8B%E4%B8%8E%E8%BF%90%E7%BB%B4%E7%AD%96%E7%95%A5%E4%BC%98%E5%8C%96%E5%9F%BA%E4%BA%8E%E6%88%90%E6%9C%AC%E6%95%88%E7%9B%8A%E7%9A%84%E7%BB%BC%E5%90%88%E5%86%B3%E7%AD%96%E6%A1%86%E6%9E%B6/image-20250303154521803_hu_f329c832a8019a0b.png 1024w&#34;
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
